      "content": "been looking at some old maps of London and man... the way some of these streets intersect near the old docks is kinda trippy. i was overlaying it with some street grids from lower manhattan and the angles are almost identical. like, it's not just a coincidence, the lines are hitting these specific points at the same degree. u think it's just urban planning stuff or is there something more to the geometry here?",
